cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper presents a system that uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for object detection and pose estimation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) categories. The use of multiple viewpoints for pose estimation suggests a potential application of machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a state-of-the-art dense Simultaneous Localisation and Mapping (SLAM) system, which could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. Finally, the paper discusses the reconstruction of room-sized environments, which could potentially fall under the graphics (cs.GR) category.
